        h3.
          What does BED feel like?
        p.
          As stated in the DSM-5, BED binges are characterized by “a sense of lack of control over eating” and “marked distress,” and adults with BED typically experience binge-related embarrassment, depression, self-disgust, and guilt. Adults with moderate, severe, or extreme BED may have these negative feelings every day, or even several times a day. No one wants to experience embarrassment, depression, self-disgust, and guilt on a consistent basis. Identifying and accurately diagnosing BED may be the first step to helping them feel better.
